# Cursor Rules - Pawel Lipowczan Portfolio Website

## Project Overview
Modern portfolio website for Pawel Lipowczan built with React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS, and Framer Motion. Features a green/teal color scheme, animated UI, and blog functionality.

## Code Style & Standards

### JavaScript/React
- Use functional components with React Hooks
- Use arrow functions for components: `const Component = () => {}`
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use destructuring for props: `const Component = ({ prop1, prop2 }) => {}`
- Use optional chaining and nullish coalescing: `data?.field ?? 'default'`
- Keep components small and focused (< 200 lines)
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Use PropTypes or TypeScript for type checking (if TypeScript is added later)

### File Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Hero.jsx`, `ProjectCard.jsx`)
- Utilities/Hooks: camelCase (e.g., `useScrollAnimation.js`, `formatDate.js`)
- Pages: PascalCase (e.g., `Home.jsx`, `BlogPost.jsx`)
- Styles: kebab-case (e.g., `global-styles.css`)
- Constants: UPPERCASE (e.g., `COLORS.js`, `API_ENDPOINTS.js`)

