### CSS/Tailwind
- Use Tailwind utility classes primarily
- Custom CSS only when necessary (complex gradients, animations)
- Use @apply for repeated utility combinations
- Mobile-first responsive design: `<div className="text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">`
- Color consistency: Use defined color palette from `tailwind.config.js`
- Avoid inline styles unless dynamic values required

### Tailwind Class Order
1. Layout (display, position, flex, grid)
2. Sizing (width, height, padding, margin)
3. Typography (font, text-size, text-color)
4. Visual (background, border, shadow)
5. Effects (opacity, transform, transition)

Example:
