## Animation Guidelines

### Framer Motion Variants
- Always use variants for complex animations
- Keep animations smooth (0.4-0.8s duration)
- Use `ease: [0.6, 0.05, 0.01, 0.9]` for smooth easing
- Implement scroll-triggered animations with `whileInView`

Example:
```jsx
const fadeInUp = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 60 },
  visible: { 
    opacity: 1, 
    y: 0,
    transition: { duration: 0.6, ease: [0.6, 0.05, 0.01, 0.9] }
  }
};

<motion.div
  variants={fadeInUp}
  initial="hidden"
  whileInView="visible"
  viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}
>
```

### Performance Optimization
- Animate only `transform` and `opacity` properties
- Use `will-change` sparingly
- Implement `viewport={{ once: true }}` for scroll animations
- Avoid animating expensive properties (width, height, etc.)

## Component Patterns

### Button Component
```jsx
const Button = ({ children, variant = 'primary', onClick, className = '' }) => {
  const baseStyles = 'px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold transition-all duration-300';
  const variants = {
    primary: 'bg-primary-500 text-dark-900 hover:bg-primary-400 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-primary-500/50',
    outline: 'border-2 border-primary-500 text-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-500 hover:text-dark-900',
  };
  
  return (
    <button 
      onClick={onClick}
      className={`${baseStyles} ${variants[variant]} ${className}`}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

