## SEO Best Practices

### Meta Tags
- Use React Helmet for dynamic meta tags
- Unique title and description per page
- Include Open Graph and Twitter Card tags
- Set canonical URLs

Example:
```jsx
import { Helmet } from 'react-helmet-async';

<Helmet>
  <title>Pawel Lipowczan - Full Stack Developer | Your Tech Guide</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Portfolio of Pawel Lipowczan, showcasing web development projects and technical blog articles." />
  <meta property="og:title" content="Pawel Lipowczan - Portfolio" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="Full Stack Developer specializing in React and Node.js" />
  <meta property="og:image" content="/og-image.jpg" />
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
</Helmet>
```

### Semantic HTML
- Use proper heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3)
- One H1 per page (main heading)
- Use semantic elements: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`
- Add descriptive alt text to all images

### URL Structure
- Clean, readable URLs: `/blog/my-article-title`
- Use slugs for blog posts
- Implement breadcrumbs for navigation

## Performance Optimization

### Image Optimization
- Use WebP format with fallbacks
- Implement lazy loading: `loading="lazy"`
- Provide multiple sizes with `srcset`
- Optimize images before upload (compress to < 200KB)

### Code Splitting
- Lazy load pages: `const Blog = lazy(() => import('./pages/Blog'))`
- Use `<Suspense>` with fallback
- Split large components if needed

### Bundle Optimization
- Keep bundle size < 200KB (gzipped)
- Tree-shake unused code
- Minimize third-party dependencies
- Use dynamic imports for heavy libraries

## Accessibility (A11y)

### Requirements
- Keyboard navigation support (Tab, Enter, Escape)
- ARIA labels on interactive elements
- Focus visible indicators
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 (text)
- Skip to content link
- Form labels and error messages

### Testing
- Test with keyboard only (no mouse)
- Use browser DevTools Accessibility panel
- Check color contrast with tools
- Test with screen reader (optional)

